WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:21.434 align:middle line:90%


00:00:21.434 --> 00:00:23.600 align:middle line:10%
>> REGINA MEREDITH: While
many people have not heard

00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:26.660 align:middle line:10%
of the 2012 phenomena
until relatively recently,

00:00:26.660 --> 00:00:29.130 align:middle line:10%
this information has been
circulating since the late

00:00:29.130 --> 00:00:32.700 align:middle line:10%
1970s and early '80s
in esoteric circles.

00:00:32.700 --> 00:00:35.510 align:middle line:10%
It was a time when psychic
phenomena was being studied

00:00:35.510 --> 00:00:38.710 align:middle line:10%
at universities, channeling
came into our awareness,

00:00:38.710 --> 00:00:42.390 align:middle line:10%
and the average person began
asking the bigger questions.

00:00:42.390 --> 00:00:45.240 align:middle line:84%
Jay Weidner has been on this
path throughout those decades

00:00:45.240 --> 00:00:47.710 align:middle line:84%
and has written extensively
on the subject of the larger

00:00:47.710 --> 00:00:50.380 align:middle line:84%
cycles of consciousness
as seen through the lens

00:00:50.380 --> 00:00:51.560 align:middle line:90%
of the ancients.

00:00:51.560 --> 00:00:54.880 align:middle line:84%
Today we speak about
2012, its cosmic roots,

00:00:54.880 --> 00:00:57.790 align:middle line:84%
and what it promises
as to our future.

00:00:57.790 --> 00:00:58.870 align:middle line:90%
This is so much fun.

00:00:58.870 --> 00:01:00.340 align:middle line:90%
This'll be a lively hour.

00:01:00.340 --> 00:01:03.080 align:middle line:84%
What I want to do today--
and this is a tall task--

00:01:03.080 --> 00:01:06.240 align:middle line:84%
is you're speaking on
behalf of the ancients, all

00:01:06.240 --> 00:01:09.520 align:middle line:84%
of the contemporary
authors on this subject,

00:01:09.520 --> 00:01:12.740 align:middle line:84%
and giving us an overview as to
all the different reflections

00:01:12.740 --> 00:01:14.390 align:middle line:90%
and visions of 2012.

00:01:14.390 --> 00:01:16.700 align:middle line:10%
But before we do that, for
anyone who doesn't already

00:01:16.700 --> 00:01:18.340 align:middle line:10%
know you, give us
a little background

00:01:18.340 --> 00:01:22.060 align:middle line:10%
as to how you became so
ensconced in this subject.

00:01:22.060 --> 00:01:24.570 align:middle line:10%
>> JAY WEIDNER: Well,
that's a good question.

00:01:24.570 --> 00:01:28.370 align:middle line:10%
Years ago, I was
living in Los Angeles,

00:01:28.370 --> 00:01:29.910 align:middle line:10%
and I attended a garage sale.

00:01:29.910 --> 00:01:32.410 align:middle line:10%
I was a book freak,
buying books.

00:01:32.410 --> 00:01:35.146 align:middle line:84%
And I found an
esoteric book sale.

00:01:35.146 --> 00:01:36.520 align:middle line:84%
Some old guy had
died, and he was

00:01:36.520 --> 00:01:39.320 align:middle line:84%
selling his books-- his
wife was-- for a $1 each.

00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:43.007 align:middle line:84%
And I bought 20 or 30 books and
went home, and one of the books

00:01:43.007 --> 00:01:44.590 align:middle line:84%
was called "Mystery
of the Cathedrals"

00:01:44.590 --> 00:01:48.220 align:middle line:84%
by an enigmatic anonymous
man named Fulcanelli.

00:01:48.220 --> 00:01:53.330 align:middle line:84%
And the book proposed that
the ancient Gothic cathedrals

00:01:53.330 --> 00:01:57.030 align:middle line:84%
were not built by the Catholic
Church or by popes or anything.

00:01:57.030 --> 00:01:59.830 align:middle line:84%
It was built by
Templars and alchemists

00:01:59.830 --> 00:02:03.390 align:middle line:84%
and that they were
homages to alchemy

00:02:03.390 --> 00:02:05.830 align:middle line:84%
and that the secret
of alchemy was

00:02:05.830 --> 00:02:09.699 align:middle line:84%
in the architecture of the
agent Gothic cathedrals.

00:02:09.699 --> 00:02:13.950 align:middle line:84%
I was a skeptic, a journalist,
believed in science and said,

00:02:13.950 --> 00:02:19.380 align:middle line:84%
this is just crap, so I began
to try to debunk the book.

00:02:19.380 --> 00:02:24.020 align:middle line:84%
And 20 years later,
the book debunked me,

00:02:24.020 --> 00:02:26.250 align:middle line:90%
and I became what I am now.

00:02:26.250 --> 00:02:30.230 align:middle line:84%
And in that book at the very
end, there's a last chapter,

00:02:30.230 --> 00:02:33.600 align:middle line:84%
and it's called "The
Cyclic Cross of Hendaye,"

00:02:33.600 --> 00:02:37.140 align:middle line:84%
and it talks about an ancient
cross, a 400-year-old cross,

00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:40.300 align:middle line:84%
which Fulcanelli
deciphers, and assures us

00:02:40.300 --> 00:02:43.410 align:middle line:84%
that it's talking about a
time in the near future.

00:02:43.410 --> 00:02:45.590 align:middle line:84%
"Mystery of the Cathedrals"
came out in 1926.

00:02:45.590 --> 00:02:47.880 align:middle line:84%
So the near future
there would come

00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:50.720 align:middle line:84%
a time of great
transformation of humanity,

00:02:50.720 --> 00:02:53.450 align:middle line:84%
and that if you decipher
the Cross of Hendaye the way

00:02:53.450 --> 00:02:56.600 align:middle line:84%
the Fulcanelli does, you'll be
able to tell the date and what

00:02:56.600 --> 00:02:57.860 align:middle line:90%
is going to happen.

00:02:57.860 --> 00:02:59.850 align:middle line:90%
So naturally, I got intrigued.

00:02:59.850 --> 00:03:02.420 align:middle line:84%
I flew to France and made sure
the cross was really there,

00:03:02.420 --> 00:03:04.870 align:middle line:90%
and I started looking into it.

00:03:04.870 --> 00:03:10.160 align:middle line:90%
And it was like a zip file.

00:03:10.160 --> 00:03:14.710 align:middle line:84%
I opened it up, and literally
10,000 tons of information

00:03:14.710 --> 00:03:19.590 align:middle line:84%
came through that I was not
even familiar with about Egypt,

00:03:19.590 --> 00:03:22.450 align:middle line:84%
about alchemy, about
the Sufis, about all

00:03:22.450 --> 00:03:23.850 align:middle line:90%
these different things.

00:03:23.850 --> 00:03:25.610 align:middle line:84%
And I thought I was
a pretty smart guy,

00:03:25.610 --> 00:03:27.484 align:middle line:84%
and when I found
out all this stuff,

00:03:27.484 --> 00:03:29.650 align:middle line:84%
I realized how little I
really knew about the world,

00:03:29.650 --> 00:03:33.030 align:middle line:84%
how maladjusted my
education had been.

00:03:33.030 --> 00:03:39.780 align:middle line:84%
So I began looking into
all aspects of esoteric art

00:03:39.780 --> 00:03:41.380 align:middle line:84%
and science in
order to understand

00:03:41.380 --> 00:03:47.406 align:middle line:84%
the Cross of Hendaye,
and in 1989, '90,

00:03:47.406 --> 00:03:51.630 align:middle line:84%
I deciphered it
almost all the way.

00:03:51.630 --> 00:03:57.710 align:middle line:84%
I realized that it was pointing
to the equinoxes of 2002

00:03:57.710 --> 00:04:01.380 align:middle line:84%
and saying that it was in the
mid-range of a 20-year cycle

00:04:01.380 --> 00:04:04.830 align:middle line:84%
that began in 1992
and ends in 2012.

00:04:04.830 --> 00:04:06.340 align:middle line:84%
And somewhere in
that time period

00:04:06.340 --> 00:04:09.950 align:middle line:84%
begins and ends
this transformation.

00:04:09.950 --> 00:04:14.180 align:middle line:84%
Now at the time I knew nothing
about the Mayan calendar

00:04:14.180 --> 00:04:16.190 align:middle line:90%
or any of this other stuff.

00:04:16.190 --> 00:04:17.975 align:middle line:84%
So I went back and
started looking,

00:04:17.975 --> 00:04:22.445 align:middle line:84%
and I realized that the Mayan
calendar was put out in baktuns

00:04:22.445 --> 00:04:26.860 align:middle line:84%
or 20-year cycles, 19.8-year
cycles, something like that,

00:04:26.860 --> 00:04:32.210 align:middle line:84%
and that the last baktun
indeed started in 1992 and ends

00:04:32.210 --> 00:04:34.897 align:middle line:90%
in 2012.

00:04:34.897 --> 00:04:37.230 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: First of all, I
want to backtrack just a sec.

00:04:37.230 --> 00:04:40.220 align:middle line:84%
Why were you intrigued
with Fulcanelli?

00:04:40.220 --> 00:04:41.750 align:middle line:84%
What kind of
knowledge did this man

00:04:41.750 --> 00:04:46.150 align:middle line:84%
possess that really set
you on such a firm path?

00:04:46.150 --> 00:04:48.220 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: The thing
that got me about "Mystery

00:04:48.220 --> 00:04:51.310 align:middle line:84%
of Cathedrals" was the
intelligence of the writer.

00:04:51.310 --> 00:04:54.320 align:middle line:84%
And it was so
overwhelming intelligent,

00:04:54.320 --> 00:04:57.990 align:middle line:84%
sort of like Stephen
Hawking on steroids,

00:04:57.990 --> 00:05:01.970 align:middle line:84%
and that I knew that
if it was a hoax it

00:05:01.970 --> 00:05:05.510 align:middle line:84%
had to be the most intelligent
hoax I've ever come against.

00:05:05.510 --> 00:05:10.032 align:middle line:84%
Two, the guy knew
things about history,

00:05:10.032 --> 00:05:11.615 align:middle line:84%
especially about the
French Revolution

00:05:11.615 --> 00:05:13.630 align:middle line:84%
and around that
time period, that

00:05:13.630 --> 00:05:15.700 align:middle line:90%
actually was impossible to know.

00:05:15.700 --> 00:05:18.100 align:middle line:84%
He knew where graffiti
was that had been removed

00:05:18.100 --> 00:05:22.600 align:middle line:84%
in the early 1800s that was in
Notre Dame Cathedral talking

00:05:22.600 --> 00:05:25.030 align:middle line:84%
about Napoleon and
the rise of Napoleon.

00:05:25.030 --> 00:05:27.600 align:middle line:84%
I thought, well,
how can this be?

00:05:27.600 --> 00:05:30.210 align:middle line:84%
And then he intimates
throughout the book

00:05:30.210 --> 00:05:34.077 align:middle line:84%
that he's several
hundred years old, right?

00:05:34.077 --> 00:05:34.660 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:05:34.660 --> 00:05:37.100 align:middle line:90%
So he is an alchemist.

00:05:37.100 --> 00:05:40.060 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: He is an
alchemist, and he was an adept,

00:05:40.060 --> 00:05:44.570 align:middle line:84%
and I believe that he was part
of a group of people who live

00:05:44.570 --> 00:05:48.490 align:middle line:84%
in the south of France who are
preserving the knowledge to be

00:05:48.490 --> 00:05:50.427 align:middle line:84%
released very slowly,
especially at this time.

00:05:50.427 --> 00:05:52.010 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Tell us
about those people.

00:05:52.010 --> 00:05:54.630 align:middle line:84%
Because I was going to ask you
if he belonged to some sect

00:05:54.630 --> 00:05:57.020 align:middle line:84%
that we may know about
that might even be cloaked

00:05:57.020 --> 00:06:00.250 align:middle line:84%
as one of the secret
societies or beyond that even,

00:06:00.250 --> 00:06:01.490 align:middle line:90%
more esoteric perhaps.

00:06:01.490 --> 00:06:02.198 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:06:02.198 --> 00:06:05.870 align:middle line:84%
What happened was was that there
was an esoteric Freemasonry

00:06:05.870 --> 00:06:08.730 align:middle line:84%
that was centered
in France, and it

00:06:08.730 --> 00:06:13.980 align:middle line:84%
was usurped in around 1750,
1770, around that time period.

00:06:13.980 --> 00:06:15.470 align:middle line:84%
We don't really
know what happened.

00:06:15.470 --> 00:06:18.280 align:middle line:84%
But this group in
France was usurped

00:06:18.280 --> 00:06:22.320 align:middle line:84%
by a British Freemasonry-- a
Scottish-British Freemasonry--

00:06:22.320 --> 00:06:25.350 align:middle line:84%
and the group in France
decided that's it.

00:06:25.350 --> 00:06:27.250 align:middle line:84%
We want nothing to
do with you guys,

00:06:27.250 --> 00:06:30.380 align:middle line:84%
we're not going to give you
our secrets, you're profane,

00:06:30.380 --> 00:06:32.580 align:middle line:84%
we're sacred, and they
disappeared and went

00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:34.990 align:middle line:84%
underground, and we've
never seen them again.

00:06:34.990 --> 00:06:39.970 align:middle line:84%
However, they're pulling the
strings of history, silently,

00:06:39.970 --> 00:06:41.504 align:middle line:90%
psychically.

00:06:41.504 --> 00:06:43.920 align:middle line:84%
What Fulcanelli says is they
come into your head at night.

00:06:43.920 --> 00:06:45.495 align:middle line:84%
They pick you out, and
they come into your head,

00:06:45.495 --> 00:06:46.470 align:middle line:90%
and they give you information.

00:06:46.470 --> 00:06:47.830 align:middle line:90%
They drop books in your lap.

00:06:47.830 --> 00:06:51.250 align:middle line:84%
They do anything they can,
because that other Freemasonry

00:06:51.250 --> 00:06:52.522 align:middle line:90%
became the Illuminati.

00:06:52.522 --> 00:06:53.230 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:06:53.230 --> 00:06:56.040 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: And so this French
Freemasonry is at war with

00:06:56.040 --> 00:07:00.160 align:middle line:84%
them-- if war is not really a
struggle-- with them for us.

00:07:00.160 --> 00:07:02.800 align:middle line:84%
And the Illuminati wants to
control us and keep us asleep.

00:07:02.800 --> 00:07:05.420 align:middle line:84%
So they're the owls, and
this group is the roosters

00:07:05.420 --> 00:07:06.850 align:middle line:90%
because they want to wake us up.

00:07:06.850 --> 00:07:08.527 align:middle line:84%
So it's the roosters
and the owls,

00:07:08.527 --> 00:07:09.860 align:middle line:90%
and they're fighting each other.

00:07:09.860 --> 00:07:12.200 align:middle line:84%
Fulcanelli is a
member of this group.

00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:17.030 align:middle line:84%
What's interesting about this is
the original Harry Potter story

00:07:17.030 --> 00:07:19.004 align:middle line:84%
is actually a story
about Fulcanelli.

00:07:19.004 --> 00:07:20.670 align:middle line:84%
I did not read the
Harry Potter stories.

00:07:20.670 --> 00:07:23.180 align:middle line:84%
I saw the first movie,
and I went to see it,

00:07:23.180 --> 00:07:25.300 align:middle line:84%
and I just literally my
jaw dropped to the ground.

00:07:25.300 --> 00:07:30.070 align:middle line:84%
Because Fulcanelli's
student, Eugene Canseliet,

00:07:30.070 --> 00:07:33.660 align:middle line:84%
received a letter in 1952,
long after Fulcanelli

00:07:33.660 --> 00:07:37.210 align:middle line:84%
had left this world, saying
come to the train station

00:07:37.210 --> 00:07:38.270 align:middle line:90%
in Seville.

00:07:38.270 --> 00:07:41.110 align:middle line:84%
It was written in an
aristocratic handwriting,

00:07:41.110 --> 00:07:44.470 align:middle line:90%
this letter, with a seal on it.

00:07:44.470 --> 00:07:45.960 align:middle line:84%
And so he went to
the train station

00:07:45.960 --> 00:07:48.610 align:middle line:84%
in Seville, just like
Harry Potter receives

00:07:48.610 --> 00:07:50.410 align:middle line:84%
a letter in
aristocratic handwriting

00:07:50.410 --> 00:07:52.710 align:middle line:84%
with a seal to go
to a train station.

00:07:52.710 --> 00:07:56.130 align:middle line:84%
Only when Eugene Canseliet
went to the train station,

00:07:56.130 --> 00:07:59.210 align:middle line:84%
he was picked up by a
limousine, blindfolded,

00:07:59.210 --> 00:08:02.630 align:middle line:84%
and taken into the Pyrenees
Mountains to a castle,

00:08:02.630 --> 00:08:06.380 align:middle line:84%
just like Harry Potter, where
they were taught esoteric arts

00:08:06.380 --> 00:08:08.490 align:middle line:84%
with children all dressed
in medieval clothing,

00:08:08.490 --> 00:08:09.950 align:middle line:90%
just like Harry Potter.

00:08:09.950 --> 00:08:10.720 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:08:10.720 --> 00:08:14.020 align:middle line:84%
And Eugene Canseliet stayed in
this place for a couple weeks,

00:08:14.020 --> 00:08:17.090 align:middle line:84%
saw Fulcanelli,
who is now 40 years

00:08:17.090 --> 00:08:20.010 align:middle line:84%
younger than he was
when he last saw him,

00:08:20.010 --> 00:08:22.760 align:middle line:84%
which was the time period
that had elapsed, or 35 years.

00:08:22.760 --> 00:08:26.790 align:middle line:84%
And Eugene Canseliet must
have failed whatever test,

00:08:26.790 --> 00:08:28.380 align:middle line:84%
because he was taken
back to the car,

00:08:28.380 --> 00:08:30.210 align:middle line:84%
blindfolded, and taken
back to the train station.

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:31.071 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: [LAUGHS]

00:08:31.071 --> 00:08:32.279 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: You failed, dude.

00:08:32.279 --> 00:08:32.668 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: You failed.

00:08:32.668 --> 00:08:33.059 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:08:33.059 --> 00:08:33.642 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:08:33.642 --> 00:08:35.150 align:middle line:84%
Now what's interesting
here is also

00:08:35.150 --> 00:08:38.990 align:middle line:84%
the Basque language has
not yet been deciphered.

00:08:38.990 --> 00:08:42.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we could say most
likely because of its proximity

00:08:42.030 --> 00:08:45.980 align:middle line:84%
to what was Atlantis, is an
ancient Atlantian language,

00:08:45.980 --> 00:08:47.140 align:middle line:90%
at least in its roots.

00:08:47.140 --> 00:08:48.050 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: That's what
they will tell you,

00:08:48.050 --> 00:08:48.710 align:middle line:90%
the Basque people.

00:08:48.710 --> 00:08:49.320 align:middle line:90%
I've talked to them.

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:49.990 align:middle line:90%
They will tell you.

00:08:49.990 --> 00:08:50.360 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: They
will tell you that.

00:08:50.360 --> 00:08:50.590 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:08:50.590 --> 00:08:52.881 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: They came from
a catastrophe somewhere west

00:08:52.881 --> 00:08:54.880 align:middle line:90%
of France, and they moved there.

00:08:54.880 --> 00:08:56.450 align:middle line:84%
And the Cross of
Hendaye is actually

00:08:56.450 --> 00:08:59.829 align:middle line:84%
the third or fourth version
of the Cross of Hendaye,

00:08:59.829 --> 00:09:01.370 align:middle line:84%
because they
deteriorate after a time

00:09:01.370 --> 00:09:03.661 align:middle line:84%
and then they build a new
one, because this information

00:09:03.661 --> 00:09:07.030 align:middle line:84%
was so important to be passed
down through these things.

00:09:07.030 --> 00:09:09.495 align:middle line:84%
And so when the alchemical
revolution started in Spain

00:09:09.495 --> 00:09:12.690 align:middle line:84%
when Islam and the
Moroccans invaded Spain,

00:09:12.690 --> 00:09:16.380 align:middle line:84%
they brought all the Arab
alchemical arts to Spain.

00:09:16.380 --> 00:09:18.750 align:middle line:84%
And Europe was-- you
couldn't read and write.

00:09:18.750 --> 00:09:19.680 align:middle line:90%
It was illegal.

00:09:19.680 --> 00:09:22.980 align:middle line:84%
The Church had outlawed all
of the reading and writing.

00:09:22.980 --> 00:09:25.010 align:middle line:84%
So all the
intellectuals of Europe

00:09:25.010 --> 00:09:26.665 align:middle line:84%
came through the
town of Hendaye--

00:09:26.665 --> 00:09:28.290 align:middle line:84%
it was the only way
around the Pyrenees

00:09:28.290 --> 00:09:30.980 align:middle line:84%
to get to Spain-- to
learn the alchemical art.

00:09:30.980 --> 00:09:36.490 align:middle line:84%
So Hendaye not only is a place
right on the border with Spain

00:09:36.490 --> 00:09:40.450 align:middle line:84%
that was a passageway back and
forth between all these adepts

00:09:40.450 --> 00:09:44.880 align:middle line:84%
going back and forth, but
its name itself, Hendaye,

00:09:44.880 --> 00:09:49.170 align:middle line:84%
is like the egg day
or the beginning day

00:09:49.170 --> 00:09:53.260 align:middle line:84%
or the day that the
rooster crows, the hen-day.

00:09:53.260 --> 00:09:56.990 align:middle line:84%
And so even it's a sign of
waking up, the name itself is.

00:09:56.990 --> 00:10:01.110 align:middle line:84%
Also, you don't pronounce the
H in French, so it's en-day.

00:10:01.110 --> 00:10:01.860 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: En-day.

00:10:01.860 --> 00:10:02.110 align:middle line:90%
End day.

00:10:02.110 --> 00:10:02.943 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: End day.

00:10:02.943 --> 00:10:03.710 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:10:03.710 --> 00:10:06.580 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: It's all
a playing on words.

00:10:06.580 --> 00:10:09.520 align:middle line:84%
Because we have to remember
that English was inculcated

00:10:09.520 --> 00:10:11.820 align:middle line:84%
by these same
alchemists, John Dee,

00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:14.050 align:middle line:84%
Francis Bacon working
with Queen Elizabeth

00:10:14.050 --> 00:10:17.060 align:middle line:84%
inculcated, through
Shakespeare, English

00:10:17.060 --> 00:10:20.936 align:middle line:84%
to be the magical
language of the future.

00:10:20.936 --> 00:10:21.560 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:10:21.560 --> 00:10:22.340 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:22.340 --> 00:10:23.950 align:middle line:84%
Now we could go
down a lot of roads

00:10:23.950 --> 00:10:25.951 align:middle line:84%
because we could get into
the inception of the--

00:10:25.951 --> 00:10:27.325 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: It
all leads to 2012.

00:10:27.325 --> 00:10:28.120 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It does.

00:10:28.120 --> 00:10:30.550 align:middle line:84%
You go back from the Freemasons
to the Knight Templars.

00:10:30.550 --> 00:10:32.940 align:middle line:84%
You start looking at very
special properties on some

00:10:32.940 --> 00:10:34.690 align:middle line:90%
of those peaks in the Pyrenees.

00:10:34.690 --> 00:10:37.440 align:middle line:84%
And we have some other intrigues
going on, but, as you say,

00:10:37.440 --> 00:10:39.970 align:middle line:84%
all roads lead back to
this period of time.

00:10:39.970 --> 00:10:44.170 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk for a
moment about 1970s,

00:10:44.170 --> 00:10:46.590 align:middle line:84%
when you were first getting
going, all these books.

00:10:46.590 --> 00:10:48.250 align:middle line:84%
There's a book that
you particularly

00:10:48.250 --> 00:10:50.084 align:middle line:84%
treasure by a man named
Frank Waters, right?

00:10:50.084 --> 00:10:50.791 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:10:50.791 --> 00:10:53.070 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And that was
the first glimpse you saw

00:10:53.070 --> 00:10:55.299 align:middle line:90%
of reference in modern times.

00:10:55.299 --> 00:10:57.840 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: What Frank Waters
did was he was one of the first

00:10:57.840 --> 00:11:01.940 align:middle line:84%
guys to go down to Mexico, and
he learned the Mayan language

00:11:01.940 --> 00:11:03.120 align:middle line:90%
and everything.

00:11:03.120 --> 00:11:06.230 align:middle line:84%
And he was an amateur
anthropologist,

00:11:06.230 --> 00:11:10.350 align:middle line:84%
and he came up against
J. Eric Thompson's work

00:11:10.350 --> 00:11:12.300 align:middle line:90%
on the Mayan calendar.

00:11:12.300 --> 00:11:16.230 align:middle line:84%
And the problem
with Mexico mystique

00:11:16.230 --> 00:11:24.680 align:middle line:84%
was that Waters was counting--
not counting the year 0.

00:11:24.680 --> 00:11:28.960 align:middle line:90%
So you have BC to AD, OK?

00:11:28.960 --> 00:11:32.370 align:middle line:84%
And what he was doing was
he was counting-- no, he

00:11:32.370 --> 00:11:37.004 align:middle line:84%
was counting the year 0 as
if it was a full year and not

00:11:37.004 --> 00:11:38.920 align:middle line:84%
the end of one and the
beginning of the other.

00:11:38.920 --> 00:11:43.830 align:middle line:84%
And he dropped it off
at December 21, 2011

00:11:43.830 --> 00:11:45.650 align:middle line:84%
because he didn't
do the count right.

00:11:45.650 --> 00:11:47.290 align:middle line:90%
You have to do a day count.

00:11:47.290 --> 00:11:49.500 align:middle line:84%
The Mayan calendar
is in a day count.

00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:54.650 align:middle line:84%
So later scholars after Waters
did the actual day count,

00:11:54.650 --> 00:11:57.680 align:middle line:84%
forgetting the
Christian calendar,

00:11:57.680 --> 00:11:59.190 align:middle line:90%
which wasn't right anyway.

00:11:59.190 --> 00:11:59.920 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: The
Gregorian calendar?

00:11:59.920 --> 00:12:00.180 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:00.180 --> 00:12:01.230 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: Gregorian calendar,
which isn't right anyway.

00:12:01.230 --> 00:12:02.320 align:middle line:84%
It's got all sorts of
days missing in it.

00:12:02.320 --> 00:12:03.655 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Oh,
interesting things there.

00:12:03.655 --> 00:12:04.050 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:12:04.050 --> 00:12:05.920 align:middle line:84%
So they just did the day
count, forgot the Christian,

00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:07.810 align:middle line:84%
forgot the Western,
just did a day count,

00:12:07.810 --> 00:12:11.280 align:middle line:84%
and you ended at
December 21, 2012, OK?

00:12:11.280 --> 00:12:12.900 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's a solstice.

00:12:12.900 --> 00:12:17.370 align:middle line:84%
That's an important sacred
date in all ancient cultures.

00:12:17.370 --> 00:12:21.940 align:middle line:84%
So this is where it
stayed for about 10 years

00:12:21.940 --> 00:12:28.050 align:middle line:84%
or so, and then in the
late '80s, early '90s, '94,

00:12:28.050 --> 00:12:32.610 align:middle line:84%
'95 around that time, they began
inventing the Voyager astronomy

00:12:32.610 --> 00:12:33.930 align:middle line:90%
software.

00:12:33.930 --> 00:12:36.300 align:middle line:84%
And an enterprising
man, who later

00:12:36.300 --> 00:12:38.860 align:middle line:84%
became a friend of mine,
John Major Jenkins, who'd

00:12:38.860 --> 00:12:41.460 align:middle line:84%
written a couple books
on the Mayans, "Tzolkin"

00:12:41.460 --> 00:12:44.950 align:middle line:84%
and a couple other books,
got the Voyager software,

00:12:44.950 --> 00:12:46.410 align:middle line:84%
and he decided
that he would look

00:12:46.410 --> 00:12:48.900 align:middle line:84%
to see what the stars
were like on December 21.

00:12:48.900 --> 00:12:50.390 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Now is this a
really pivotal event that this

00:12:50.390 --> 00:12:51.160 align:middle line:90%
software existed?

00:12:51.160 --> 00:12:51.910 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: It is.

00:12:51.910 --> 00:12:53.050 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: OK.

00:12:53.050 --> 00:12:56.810 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: Because you could
do it with armillary spheres,

00:12:56.810 --> 00:12:59.180 align:middle line:84%
like Nostradamus did,
but it doesn't tell you--

00:12:59.180 --> 00:13:01.190 align:middle line:90%
it's not as exact as software.

00:13:01.190 --> 00:13:04.120 align:middle line:84%
So he typed in
December 21, 2012,

00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:06.400 align:middle line:84%
and he went, and
he looked to see.

00:13:06.400 --> 00:13:09.430 align:middle line:84%
And then he saw that
the center of the galaxy

00:13:09.430 --> 00:13:14.600 align:middle line:84%
was crossing the rising sun on
that morning at 11:11 Universal

00:13:14.600 --> 00:13:15.870 align:middle line:90%
Standard Time.

00:13:15.870 --> 00:13:18.430 align:middle line:84%
And he went, oh my god,
what does this mean?

00:13:18.430 --> 00:13:20.430 align:middle line:84%
How could the
Mayans-- did they know

00:13:20.430 --> 00:13:23.849 align:middle line:84%
that the center of the galaxy
and the sun and the Earth

00:13:23.849 --> 00:13:25.390 align:middle line:84%
were all going to
be all in one line?

00:13:25.390 --> 00:13:26.181 align:middle line:90%
Did they know that?

00:13:26.181 --> 00:13:27.520 align:middle line:90%
How could they know that?

00:13:27.520 --> 00:13:31.340 align:middle line:84%
And so then he began
back-engineering this,

00:13:31.340 --> 00:13:34.700 align:middle line:84%
and he realized that, in
fact, on a mountaintop,

00:13:34.700 --> 00:13:39.184 align:middle line:84%
like Guatemala, southern
Mexico, on a clear night,

00:13:39.184 --> 00:13:41.100 align:middle line:84%
you can actually see the
center of the galaxy.

00:13:41.100 --> 00:13:43.980 align:middle line:90%
It's like a big cloud of stars.

00:13:43.980 --> 00:13:48.510 align:middle line:84%
And he realized that
someone with a good eyesight

00:13:48.510 --> 00:13:52.710 align:middle line:84%
could actually extrapolate
with triangulation

00:13:52.710 --> 00:13:56.090 align:middle line:84%
and come and realize when
that center of the galaxy

00:13:56.090 --> 00:13:58.600 align:middle line:84%
was going to rise
up, at what time,

00:13:58.600 --> 00:14:00.770 align:middle line:84%
and hit the sun
when it was rising

00:14:00.770 --> 00:14:02.630 align:middle line:90%
so they'd rise at the same time.

00:14:02.630 --> 00:14:07.995 align:middle line:84%
And they built the calendar
around that event, OK?

00:14:07.995 --> 00:14:11.340 align:middle line:84%
Now the thing that's important
is that they're seers.

00:14:11.340 --> 00:14:17.020 align:middle line:84%
The Mayan seers
were time travelers.

00:14:17.020 --> 00:14:20.370 align:middle line:84%
They used magic mushrooms, and
they traveled into the future.

00:14:20.370 --> 00:14:23.740 align:middle line:84%
We know this from their myths
and from the "Popol Vuh."

00:14:23.740 --> 00:14:28.300 align:middle line:84%
And so what we believe is
that, just like Nostradamus

00:14:28.300 --> 00:14:34.040 align:middle line:84%
and all seers, they all went
to the future, these diviners,

00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:36.500 align:middle line:84%
and they saw
something happening.

00:14:36.500 --> 00:14:39.000 align:middle line:84%
And they said, whoa,
this is so important we

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:41.570 align:middle line:84%
have to build a
calendar around it.

00:14:41.570 --> 00:14:44.350 align:middle line:84%
And this is what
Jenkins' conclusion was.

00:14:44.350 --> 00:14:47.020 align:middle line:84%
It's not the alignment itself
that's causing the event,

00:14:47.020 --> 00:14:49.234 align:middle line:84%
just like noon on
the clock doesn't

00:14:49.234 --> 00:14:50.775 align:middle line:84%
mean you have to--
time to eat lunch.

00:14:50.775 --> 00:14:52.425 align:middle line:84%
You eat lunch when
you're hungry.

00:14:52.425 --> 00:14:54.050 align:middle line:84%
It just happens that
you're hungry when

00:14:54.050 --> 00:14:56.650 align:middle line:84%
the two things are
pointing up, OK?

00:14:56.650 --> 00:14:58.880 align:middle line:84%
So when this alignment
happens, it's

00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:00.780 align:middle line:84%
not necessarily
causing the event.

00:15:00.780 --> 00:15:03.380 align:middle line:84%
It's just that's the time on the
clock, the great cosmic clock

00:15:03.380 --> 00:15:04.430 align:middle line:90%
we're watching.

00:15:04.430 --> 00:15:07.426 align:middle line:84%
And so they said we've
got to make a calendar

00:15:07.426 --> 00:15:08.800 align:middle line:84%
and tell our people
in the future

00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:12.450 align:middle line:84%
that this dramatic event
is coming down line.

00:15:12.450 --> 00:15:14.880 align:middle line:84%
So I met John
Jenkins right when he

00:15:14.880 --> 00:15:16.987 align:middle line:90%
was finishing his book in '98.

00:15:16.987 --> 00:15:18.320 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Is it "Cosmogenesis"?

00:15:18.320 --> 00:15:20.111 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah, "Maya
Cosmogenesis 2012."

00:15:20.111 --> 00:15:22.350 align:middle line:84%
And I had just finished
my book, "The Mysteries

00:15:22.350 --> 00:15:24.020 align:middle line:90%
of the Great Cross of Hendaye."

00:15:24.020 --> 00:15:25.990 align:middle line:84%
And so we were living
in the same city,

00:15:25.990 --> 00:15:28.060 align:middle line:90%
and we began talking.

00:15:28.060 --> 00:15:30.099 align:middle line:84%
And he was blown
away by my research,

00:15:30.099 --> 00:15:31.640 align:middle line:84%
and I was blown away
by his research.

00:15:31.640 --> 00:15:35.320 align:middle line:84%
And then I decided that one
of the leads that I had gotten

00:15:35.320 --> 00:15:37.580 align:middle line:84%
from the Great
Cross of Hendaye was

00:15:37.580 --> 00:15:41.660 align:middle line:84%
that there was a cross in Peru,
where the same symbols were

00:15:41.660 --> 00:15:43.560 align:middle line:90%
on that cross.

00:15:43.560 --> 00:15:45.230 align:middle line:84%
So I went to Peru
to find that cross,

00:15:45.230 --> 00:15:49.130 align:middle line:84%
and I found a cross that
had been broken and defaced.

00:15:49.130 --> 00:15:50.560 align:middle line:90%
So I did not find the cross.

00:15:50.560 --> 00:15:53.930 align:middle line:84%
But what I did find was the
Incan people and the Q'ero

00:15:53.930 --> 00:15:56.450 align:middle line:84%
people, and so I
began talking to them.

00:15:56.450 --> 00:15:59.120 align:middle line:84%
And they told me that they
have a prophecy about 2012.

00:15:59.120 --> 00:16:04.400 align:middle line:90%
Now this is '98 now, '98.

00:16:04.400 --> 00:16:07.200 align:middle line:84%
So I spent many hours talking
to them in their hut, these two

00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:09.990 align:middle line:84%
shamans, and they call
it the Pachacuti, which

00:16:09.990 --> 00:16:14.130 align:middle line:84%
means the tearing of
the veil between worlds

00:16:14.130 --> 00:16:16.810 align:middle line:84%
that would begin
happening in 2012.

00:16:16.810 --> 00:16:21.290 align:middle line:84%
And they said that it would
start in the United States,

00:16:21.290 --> 00:16:22.770 align:middle line:84%
that for some
reason this was all

00:16:22.770 --> 00:16:24.820 align:middle line:84%
going to be based in
the United States,

00:16:24.820 --> 00:16:26.620 align:middle line:84%
and that the United
States was going

00:16:26.620 --> 00:16:31.770 align:middle line:84%
to learn how to change
from a people of the brain

00:16:31.770 --> 00:16:34.120 align:middle line:84%
to a people of the
heart, and that

00:16:34.120 --> 00:16:37.400 align:middle line:84%
would lead the world to
this next thing that's

00:16:37.400 --> 00:16:39.770 align:middle line:90%
going to happen.

00:16:39.770 --> 00:16:46.450 align:middle line:84%
It will start in 1992 and
will go on to 2030 or 2035

00:16:46.450 --> 00:16:50.480 align:middle line:84%
before this is over, an
incredibly tumultuous time,

00:16:50.480 --> 00:16:54.120 align:middle line:84%
which will appear to most
of the people living in it

00:16:54.120 --> 00:16:55.750 align:middle line:90%
like it's the end of the world.

00:16:55.750 --> 00:16:57.319 align:middle line:84%
But to the
enlightened ones, they

00:16:57.319 --> 00:16:59.360 align:middle line:84%
will see that, no, it's
not the end of the world.

00:16:59.360 --> 00:17:01.224 align:middle line:90%
It's the beginning of the world.

00:17:01.224 --> 00:17:02.890 align:middle line:84%
It just looks like
the end of the world.

00:17:02.890 --> 00:17:04.380 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And what you're
saying is really key,

00:17:04.380 --> 00:17:06.980 align:middle line:84%
this whole notion that we move
from the head to the heart.

00:17:06.980 --> 00:17:07.290 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Right.

00:17:07.290 --> 00:17:09.289 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And we can
already see this happening

00:17:09.289 --> 00:17:10.270 align:middle line:90%
in the United States.

00:17:10.270 --> 00:17:10.740 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: We can.

00:17:10.740 --> 00:17:12.156 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: No
matter where you go,

00:17:12.156 --> 00:17:16.940 align:middle line:84%
people are starting to say of
all ages that this is painful.

00:17:16.940 --> 00:17:20.839 align:middle line:84%
Life has become dry and
heartless and painful.

00:17:20.839 --> 00:17:21.880 align:middle line:90%
You hear that everywhere.

00:17:21.880 --> 00:17:22.569 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yep.

00:17:22.569 --> 00:17:25.130 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And so the tearing
down of these structures is

00:17:25.130 --> 00:17:27.050 align:middle line:84%
really what they
were talking about.

00:17:27.050 --> 00:17:29.290 align:middle line:84%
We're going to go through
each of these beings, each

00:17:29.290 --> 00:17:32.050 align:middle line:84%
of these different, well,
people and also societies

00:17:32.050 --> 00:17:34.540 align:middle line:84%
and talk about their
specific vision

00:17:34.540 --> 00:17:37.280 align:middle line:84%
as to what had to
be torn asunder

00:17:37.280 --> 00:17:39.160 align:middle line:90%
and what has to take its place.

00:17:39.160 --> 00:17:41.820 align:middle line:84%
So let's start with
the Mayan and how

00:17:41.820 --> 00:17:44.810 align:middle line:84%
they visioned what this
period would look like

00:17:44.810 --> 00:17:47.230 align:middle line:84%
and what would have
to be given way to.

00:17:47.230 --> 00:17:48.050 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:17:48.050 --> 00:17:50.500 align:middle line:84%
The thing that's important to
understand about all of this

00:17:50.500 --> 00:17:56.680 align:middle line:84%
is that human beings, I hate to
say it, are basically lazy, OK?

00:17:56.680 --> 00:18:00.610 align:middle line:84%
And they won't really get off
the couch unless they have to.

00:18:00.610 --> 00:18:01.990 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: We
learn through pain.

00:18:01.990 --> 00:18:02.240 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: We do.

00:18:02.240 --> 00:18:02.810 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Sadly, we
learn through pain.

00:18:02.810 --> 00:18:03.690 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Exactly.

00:18:03.690 --> 00:18:07.950 align:middle line:84%
And it's through catastrophe-- a
divorce, death of a loved one--

00:18:07.950 --> 00:18:12.610 align:middle line:84%
that you shed old
possibilities and begin

00:18:12.610 --> 00:18:14.150 align:middle line:90%
to look at new possibilities.

00:18:14.150 --> 00:18:16.050 align:middle line:84%
It's the painful
thing that caused it.

00:18:16.050 --> 00:18:19.370 align:middle line:84%
And believe me, getting fired
from a job can be terrible,

00:18:19.370 --> 00:18:22.410 align:middle line:84%
but actually it can also
be a liberating experience.

00:18:22.410 --> 00:18:26.050 align:middle line:84%
And so what happened is
is that this thing that's

00:18:26.050 --> 00:18:30.220 align:middle line:84%
happening in 2012 had to
be preceded by catastrophe.

00:18:30.220 --> 00:18:32.565 align:middle line:84%
So I was waiting for a
catastrophe to happen.

00:18:32.565 --> 00:18:33.271 align:middle line:90%
Honestly, I was.

00:18:33.271 --> 00:18:35.520 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You could say
it's a train wreck right now.

00:18:35.520 --> 00:18:36.020 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: It is.

00:18:36.020 --> 00:18:37.050 align:middle line:90%
We're in the train wreck.

00:18:37.050 --> 00:18:37.630 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: We're
in the train wreck.

00:18:37.630 --> 00:18:38.370 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:40.440 align:middle line:84%
And so I predicted
that there was

00:18:40.440 --> 00:18:42.910 align:middle line:84%
going to be a catastrophe
on The History Channel

00:18:42.910 --> 00:18:46.030 align:middle line:84%
and on all these TV shows and
everything, and it happened.

00:18:46.030 --> 00:18:48.682 align:middle line:84%
And everybody thought I was
some kind of prognosticator.

00:18:48.682 --> 00:18:50.140 align:middle line:84%
All you had do is
look at the world

00:18:50.140 --> 00:18:52.056 align:middle line:84%
to know that this thing
was not going to last.

00:18:52.056 --> 00:18:53.290 align:middle line:90%
It was not sustainable.

00:18:53.290 --> 00:18:53.790 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:18:53.790 --> 00:18:56.560 align:middle line:84%
So now we're in the catastrophe,
starting in 2008-- really

00:18:56.560 --> 00:18:57.751 align:middle line:90%
starting in 2001.

00:18:57.751 --> 00:18:59.500 align:middle line:84%
Now 2008, we're really
in the thick of it.

00:18:59.500 --> 00:19:01.166 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And this
is important to say,

00:19:01.166 --> 00:19:04.780 align:middle line:84%
because a lot of people were
waiting for the big polarity

00:19:04.780 --> 00:19:07.760 align:middle line:84%
shift where
everything goes dark.

00:19:07.760 --> 00:19:11.310 align:middle line:84%
Most of the people on the planet
end up deceased and the like.

00:19:11.310 --> 00:19:13.300 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have to be
that dramatic at all.

00:19:13.300 --> 00:19:16.480 align:middle line:84%
The reality is our
survival is oriented

00:19:16.480 --> 00:19:21.110 align:middle line:84%
toward the systems that
exist, toward money, security.

00:19:21.110 --> 00:19:22.660 align:middle line:84%
Those things have
been torn asunder.

00:19:22.660 --> 00:19:23.090 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: They're
all going away.

00:19:23.090 --> 00:19:25.756 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And is this more what
you were referring to was these

00:19:25.756 --> 00:19:29.661 align:middle line:84%
systems, not necessarily
the natural cataclysms?

00:19:29.661 --> 00:19:31.910 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: Actually, I think
there could be a natural

00:19:31.910 --> 00:19:32.210 align:middle line:90%
cataclysm.

00:19:32.210 --> 00:19:34.070 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to deny
that that could happen.

00:19:34.070 --> 00:19:35.520 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Well, we have
a lot of activity, yeah.

00:19:35.520 --> 00:19:36.670 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: But we are natural.

00:19:36.670 --> 00:19:36.900 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah.

00:19:36.900 --> 00:19:38.290 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: And so we're
having a cataclysm,

00:19:38.290 --> 00:19:39.430 align:middle line:90%
so it's a natural cataclysm.

00:19:39.430 --> 00:19:40.055 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:19:40.055 --> 00:19:43.770 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: And so
we let it happen.

00:19:43.770 --> 00:19:45.840 align:middle line:84%
Just like some people
let a divorce happen,

00:19:45.840 --> 00:19:47.642 align:middle line:84%
they know their marriage
is falling apart,

00:19:47.642 --> 00:19:49.100 align:middle line:84%
but they don't do
anything about it

00:19:49.100 --> 00:19:52.364 align:middle line:84%
because they kind of secretly
want it to end disastrously,

00:19:52.364 --> 00:19:54.030 align:middle line:84%
because then that way
they're liberated.

00:19:54.030 --> 00:19:55.340 align:middle line:90%
That's what we're in right now.

00:19:55.340 --> 00:19:59.720 align:middle line:84%
We are falling into a
disaster of our own making,

00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:03.543 align:middle line:84%
and it's going to force
us to find our way out

00:20:03.543 --> 00:20:06.402 align:middle line:84%
of it by being in
the disaster itself.

00:20:06.402 --> 00:20:07.110 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:20:07.110 --> 00:20:09.401 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is, you mentioned
something a moment ago,

00:20:09.401 --> 00:20:12.340 align:middle line:84%
because we allowed it to
happen, because we chose it,

00:20:12.340 --> 00:20:14.890 align:middle line:84%
there was talk at that
time-- I know even

00:20:14.890 --> 00:20:18.450 align:middle line:84%
in the esoteric circles I was
in 30 years ago, 20 years ago--

00:20:18.450 --> 00:20:20.940 align:middle line:90%
that we could change.

00:20:20.940 --> 00:20:22.900 align:middle line:84%
We had the power to
cha-- and I didn't really

00:20:22.900 --> 00:20:25.030 align:middle line:84%
fully grock it
until more recently.

00:20:25.030 --> 00:20:28.270 align:middle line:84%
We had the power to change
some of these outcomes,

00:20:28.270 --> 00:20:31.900 align:middle line:84%
even in terms of physical
cataclysms on the planet,

00:20:31.900 --> 00:20:34.849 align:middle line:84%
had we been able to ratchet it
up in our own consciousness.

00:20:34.849 --> 00:20:35.890 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: That's right.

00:20:35.890 --> 00:20:39.100 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And it was even said
in a couple of places that,

00:20:39.100 --> 00:20:40.920 align:middle line:84%
had we been able
to rise to that,

00:20:40.920 --> 00:20:43.805 align:middle line:84%
there are certain events
that would have been avoided

00:20:43.805 --> 00:20:44.305 align:middle line:90%
physically.

00:20:44.305 --> 00:20:44.720 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: That's right.

00:20:44.720 --> 00:20:46.178 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Whether
they're tsunami,

00:20:46.178 --> 00:20:49.620 align:middle line:84%
whether they're earthquakes that
have yet to be, we don't know.

00:20:49.620 --> 00:20:50.620 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: We don't.

00:20:50.620 --> 00:20:52.310 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: There may be
some that have been averted.

00:20:52.310 --> 00:20:52.820 align:middle line:90%
We don't know.

00:20:52.820 --> 00:20:53.903 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: We don't know.

00:20:53.903 --> 00:20:54.814 align:middle line:90%
I think there have.

00:20:54.814 --> 00:20:56.480 align:middle line:84%
I think the fact that
we went through 40

00:20:56.480 --> 00:20:59.770 align:middle line:84%
years of a nuclear stare
down with the Soviet Union

00:20:59.770 --> 00:21:02.150 align:middle line:84%
and we didn't have anything
go off or anything happen,

00:21:02.150 --> 00:21:04.320 align:middle line:90%
I think we changed the timeline.

00:21:04.320 --> 00:21:06.170 align:middle line:90%
And we can change the timeline.

00:21:06.170 --> 00:21:08.770 align:middle line:84%
It's possible to
change the future,

00:21:08.770 --> 00:21:10.560 align:middle line:84%
if you so desire to
change the future.

00:21:10.560 --> 00:21:12.750 align:middle line:84%
Because the future
is in the now.

00:21:12.750 --> 00:21:15.524 align:middle line:84%
You change your timeline now,
and then the future is changed.

00:21:15.524 --> 00:21:16.940 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: Stephen
Hawking, right?

00:21:16.940 --> 00:21:17.990 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: That's right.

00:21:17.990 --> 00:21:20.360 align:middle line:84%
That's what this is
really all about.

00:21:20.360 --> 00:21:23.890 align:middle line:84%
There's never been a year in the
history of the human race that

00:21:23.890 --> 00:21:26.775 align:middle line:84%
has been greeted with more
anticipation than 2012.

00:21:26.775 --> 00:21:27.570 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yes.

00:21:27.570 --> 00:21:28.195 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: OK?

00:21:28.195 --> 00:21:30.090 align:middle line:84%
There was a collective
consciousness

00:21:30.090 --> 00:21:33.170 align:middle line:84%
was focusing in on a year in,
which never really happened

00:21:33.170 --> 00:21:33.960 align:middle line:90%
before.

00:21:33.960 --> 00:21:37.556 align:middle line:84%
And maybe 2000, the
year 2000 millennium.

00:21:37.556 --> 00:21:39.180 align:middle line:84%
But this was more of
a spiritual thing,

00:21:39.180 --> 00:21:42.470 align:middle line:84%
and it wasn't hooked to, like,
2 with three 0's behind it.

00:21:42.470 --> 00:21:43.530 align:middle line:90%
It was an odd year.

00:21:43.530 --> 00:21:46.990 align:middle line:84%
Why is the whole world getting
in such a ruff over this year?

00:21:46.990 --> 00:21:48.490 align:middle line:84%
And we're concentrating
on the year,

00:21:48.490 --> 00:21:51.722 align:middle line:84%
and we're saying to ourselves,
well, what do we want to be?

00:21:51.722 --> 00:21:53.430 align:middle line:84%
We're looking into
the future and saying,

00:21:53.430 --> 00:21:54.346 align:middle line:90%
what do we want to be?

00:21:54.346 --> 00:21:56.090 align:middle line:90%
Where are we going to be?

00:21:56.090 --> 00:21:57.540 align:middle line:90%
What are we going to be?

00:21:57.540 --> 00:21:59.490 align:middle line:84%
And that's never
happened before.

00:21:59.490 --> 00:22:02.910 align:middle line:84%
And the other thing that's going
on here which cannot be denied

00:22:02.910 --> 00:22:07.160 align:middle line:84%
is that exactly 20 years
ago, one baktun ago,

00:22:07.160 --> 00:22:10.480 align:middle line:84%
in 1992 was also the
beginning of the internet,

00:22:10.480 --> 00:22:13.810 align:middle line:84%
which has just destroyed the
old paradigms completely.

00:22:13.810 --> 00:22:15.520 align:middle line:84%
Just as surely as
Gutenberg's press

00:22:15.520 --> 00:22:19.250 align:middle line:84%
destroyed the Catholic Church
and in the royalty of Europe,

00:22:19.250 --> 00:22:23.370 align:middle line:84%
so too will the internet destroy
the politicians and the bankers

00:22:23.370 --> 00:22:25.000 align:middle line:84%
and everything that's
going on today.

00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:29.720 align:middle line:84%
So the internet has not
smartened us up yet,

00:22:29.720 --> 00:22:32.420 align:middle line:84%
but it's putting us on
the road to smartening up.

00:22:32.420 --> 00:22:33.900 align:middle line:90%
That's what's really going on.

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:37.080 align:middle line:84%
We will achieve wisdom,
collective wisdom,

00:22:37.080 --> 00:22:39.780 align:middle line:90%
by 2020, 2025.

00:22:39.780 --> 00:22:42.421 align:middle line:84%
The world is going to be
very, very different place.

00:22:42.421 --> 00:22:43.420 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: It has to be.

00:22:43.420 --> 00:22:43.910 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: It will be.

00:22:43.910 --> 00:22:45.840 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: If the frequencies
of the planet are changing,

00:22:45.840 --> 00:22:48.570 align:middle line:84%
if we're going through a literal
dimensional or subdimensional,

00:22:48.570 --> 00:22:52.250 align:middle line:84%
depending on who you listen
to, shift to a higher order,

00:22:52.250 --> 00:22:54.630 align:middle line:84%
you can't be on the planet
unless you keep in step

00:22:54.630 --> 00:22:55.950 align:middle line:90%
on a vibrational level, right?

00:22:55.950 --> 00:22:57.850 align:middle line:90%
So consciousness has to change.

00:22:57.850 --> 00:22:59.320 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: I would think that
maybe a lot of people are going

00:22:59.320 --> 00:23:01.615 align:middle line:84%
to die, actually, because
they're not going to be able

00:23:01.615 --> 00:23:04.290 align:middle line:84%
to handle the
changes and the vibe.

00:23:04.290 --> 00:23:08.510 align:middle line:84%
But for us, it's going to be--
the ones who are greeting it

00:23:08.510 --> 00:23:11.110 align:middle line:84%
with exaltation and
enthusiasm, it's

00:23:11.110 --> 00:23:12.780 align:middle line:84%
going to be a really
wonderful world.

00:23:12.780 --> 00:23:16.520 align:middle line:84%
And that's my message is
greet it with happiness,

00:23:16.520 --> 00:23:18.630 align:middle line:84%
because there's nothing
you can do about it.

00:23:18.630 --> 00:23:18.970 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Exactly.

00:23:18.970 --> 00:23:20.160 align:middle line:84%
>> WEIDNER: Get in there
and try to change it.

00:23:20.160 --> 00:23:20.550 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: So get
excited about it--

00:23:20.550 --> 00:23:20.920 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Exactly.

00:23:20.920 --> 00:23:22.530 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: --and then dream
about what's on the other side

00:23:22.530 --> 00:23:23.330 align:middle line:90%
of this period of time.

00:23:23.330 --> 00:23:24.180 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: What can we do here?

00:23:24.180 --> 00:23:25.600 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: I totally
agree with you.

00:23:25.600 --> 00:23:26.020 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:23:26.020 --> 00:23:27.730 align:middle line:84%
We've talked a little
bit about the Maya.

00:23:27.730 --> 00:23:30.720 align:middle line:84%
John Major Jenkins also
felt that this was not

00:23:30.720 --> 00:23:33.420 align:middle line:84%
going to be a tipping
point in terms

00:23:33.420 --> 00:23:37.280 align:middle line:84%
of physical cataclysm but
an internal consciousness

00:23:37.280 --> 00:23:39.490 align:middle line:84%
cataclysmic event
that would then

00:23:39.490 --> 00:23:41.250 align:middle line:84%
help us transform
ourselves, right?

00:23:41.250 --> 00:23:41.586 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:23:41.586 --> 00:23:41.890 align:middle line:90%
I agree.

00:23:41.890 --> 00:23:42.260 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: That was his.

00:23:42.260 --> 00:23:44.110 align:middle line:84%
Now let's talk about
Jose Arguelles,

00:23:44.110 --> 00:23:46.410 align:middle line:84%
because he's really
central to this story,

00:23:46.410 --> 00:23:48.560 align:middle line:84%
and we love what he
brought to the world.

00:23:48.560 --> 00:23:49.880 align:middle line:90%
He's no longer with us now.

00:23:49.880 --> 00:23:50.880 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah, he is.

00:23:50.880 --> 00:23:53.670 align:middle line:84%
Jose was a-- People
get irritated by Jose,

00:23:53.670 --> 00:23:55.470 align:middle line:90%
or they did when he was alive.

00:23:55.470 --> 00:23:57.380 align:middle line:84%
And I would always
say, you know what?

00:23:57.380 --> 00:23:59.600 align:middle line:84%
You're not approaching
Jose the right way.

00:23:59.600 --> 00:24:00.850 align:middle line:90%
Jose is an artist.

00:24:00.850 --> 00:24:01.725 align:middle line:90%
He's not a scientist.

00:24:01.725 --> 00:24:02.433 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Right.

00:24:02.433 --> 00:24:03.510 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: This is art.

00:24:03.510 --> 00:24:04.260 align:middle line:90%
This is art.

00:24:04.260 --> 00:24:09.390 align:middle line:84%
You're judging art
by the same premium

00:24:09.390 --> 00:24:11.750 align:middle line:90%
that you judge science or truth.

00:24:11.750 --> 00:24:12.440 align:middle line:90%
This is art.

00:24:12.440 --> 00:24:17.020 align:middle line:84%
This is consciousness
transmuted through art,

00:24:17.020 --> 00:24:19.280 align:middle line:90%
and his books are works of art.

00:24:19.280 --> 00:24:26.850 align:middle line:84%
And so Jose was brilliant
at evoking the intuitive

00:24:26.850 --> 00:24:29.960 align:middle line:84%
nature of 2012 and what's
going to happen here

00:24:29.960 --> 00:24:34.385 align:middle line:84%
on a not just indigenous
but deep down in the heart.

00:24:34.385 --> 00:24:36.060 align:middle line:84%
And he knew what
was going to happen,

00:24:36.060 --> 00:24:39.630 align:middle line:84%
so he created his books and
his calendars and things

00:24:39.630 --> 00:24:42.230 align:middle line:84%
so that this transition
would be easier.

00:24:42.230 --> 00:24:44.290 align:middle line:84%
Was Jose always
correct on everything?

00:24:44.290 --> 00:24:45.090 align:middle line:90%
No, he wasn't.

00:24:45.090 --> 00:24:46.060 align:middle line:90%
None of us are.

00:24:46.060 --> 00:24:49.480 align:middle line:84%
But was he in his
heart showing us

00:24:49.480 --> 00:24:52.900 align:middle line:84%
the path towards what
we want to be post-2012?

00:24:52.900 --> 00:24:53.910 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:24:53.910 --> 00:24:57.370 align:middle line:84%
We want to do the moon
calendar is a brilliant idea.

00:24:57.370 --> 00:24:59.820 align:middle line:84%
We should be going back
to the cycles of the moon,

00:24:59.820 --> 00:25:01.930 align:middle line:84%
getting away from the
solar calendar, which

00:25:01.930 --> 00:25:03.314 align:middle line:90%
is what he advocated.

00:25:03.314 --> 00:25:05.730 align:middle line:84%
All the things that he was
talking about-- the destruction

00:25:05.730 --> 00:25:08.110 align:middle line:84%
of the capitalist
system is going

00:25:08.110 --> 00:25:10.830 align:middle line:84%
to happen-- the whole
thing is going to happen.

00:25:10.830 --> 00:25:13.050 align:middle line:84%
It's just not going
to be quite as

00:25:13.050 --> 00:25:15.260 align:middle line:90%
easy as Jose made it out to be.

00:25:15.260 --> 00:25:16.380 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Yeah, exactly.

00:25:16.380 --> 00:25:18.970 align:middle line:84%
And Jose was really-- we
have to remember, too,

00:25:18.970 --> 00:25:22.790 align:middle line:84%
that everything that's been left
for us is in the form of art.

00:25:22.790 --> 00:25:25.136 align:middle line:84%
The artists were the
visionaries and the mystics.

00:25:25.136 --> 00:25:26.010 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: They are.

00:25:26.010 --> 00:25:28.160 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And so he
came in, his purpose.

00:25:28.160 --> 00:25:31.650 align:middle line:84%
He understood his purpose,
what now, 55, 60 years ago

00:25:31.650 --> 00:25:34.310 align:middle line:84%
when he almost was
nailed to the ground when

00:25:34.310 --> 00:25:36.010 align:middle line:84%
he first experienced
Machu Picchu

00:25:36.010 --> 00:25:38.137 align:middle line:84%
and knew what his
life was about,

00:25:38.137 --> 00:25:39.720 align:middle line:84%
what he was supposed
to bring forward.

00:25:39.720 --> 00:25:42.940 align:middle line:84%
And as an artist, a
brilliant artist and poet,

00:25:42.940 --> 00:25:45.100 align:middle line:84%
I think he did a
world of service

00:25:45.100 --> 00:25:46.980 align:middle line:84%
in creating the
beautiful view of what

00:25:46.980 --> 00:25:48.117 align:middle line:90%
the potential is in this.

00:25:48.117 --> 00:25:48.950 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: I agree.

00:25:48.950 --> 00:25:51.600 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: And the thing you
talked about a bit ago, too--

00:25:51.600 --> 00:25:54.690 align:middle line:84%
I did an interview with him just
before he died about calendar,

00:25:54.690 --> 00:25:58.790 align:middle line:84%
and I asked him this, and he was
a little taken back to answer.

00:25:58.790 --> 00:26:03.840 align:middle line:84%
And I said, Jose, when you
speak of the Gregorian calendar

00:26:03.840 --> 00:26:05.750 align:middle line:84%
versus the Mayan
calendar, he said

00:26:05.750 --> 00:26:07.582 align:middle line:84%
the problem is it
puts us completely out

00:26:07.582 --> 00:26:08.540 align:middle line:90%
of sync with ourselves.

00:26:08.540 --> 00:26:08.940 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: That's right.

00:26:08.940 --> 00:26:11.380 align:middle line:84%
>> REGINA: You can't have
unnatural cycles and still feel

00:26:11.380 --> 00:26:13.690 align:middle line:84%
any internal
coherence of rhythm.

00:26:13.690 --> 00:26:18.320 align:middle line:84%
And then he said-- I said to
him, was this done by design?

00:26:18.320 --> 00:26:21.890 align:middle line:84%
Were there those who were
intending to keep humanity out

00:26:21.890 --> 00:26:25.530 align:middle line:84%
of our own rhythm, and thus
your commitment to promoting

00:26:25.530 --> 00:26:28.360 align:middle line:84%
the Mayan calendar and
natural cycles of life?

00:26:28.360 --> 00:26:31.667 align:middle line:84%
And he said, yes, I do
believe those people did it

00:26:31.667 --> 00:26:32.250 align:middle line:90%
intentionally.

00:26:32.250 --> 00:26:33.010 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: I agree.

00:26:33.010 --> 00:26:33.790 align:middle line:90%
>> REGINA: Do you?

00:26:33.790 --> 00:26:34.748 align:middle line:90%
>> WEIDNER: Yeah, I do.

00:26:34.748 --> 00:26:36.520 align:middle line:10%
I think that they
have done everything

00:26:36.520 --> 00:26:40.710 align:middle line:10%
they can, whoever they are,
to throw us out of nature,

00:26:40.710 --> 00:26:43.160 align:middle line:10%
to get as far away from
nature as possible.

00:26:43.160 --> 00:26:45.100 align:middle line:10%
If I didn't know better,
I'd say the people

00:26:45.100 --> 00:26:48.320 align:middle line:10%
that run the world hate nature,
I mean absolutely hate it,

00:26:48.320 --> 00:26:49.550 align:middle line:10%
just hate it.

00:26:49.550 --> 00:26:50.670 align:middle line:90%
They think it's dirty.

00:26:50.670 --> 00:26:51.470 align:middle line:90%
It's filthy.

00:26:51.470 --> 00:26:52.530 align:middle line:90%
It's got insects.

00:26:52.530 --> 00:26:53.460 align:middle line:90%
It gets you dirty.

00:26:53.460 --> 00:26:54.780 align:middle line:90%
The food is bad.

00:26:54.780 --> 00:26:55.369 align:middle line:90%
I really do.

00:26:55.369 --> 00:26:57.660 align:middle line:84%
I think there's something
wrong with the people running

00:26:57.660 --> 00:27:02.040 align:middle line:84%
the world, and they have
no feeling for nature.

